The Security Council document 2093 (2013) Annex lists the following items subject to restrictions:

1. Surface to air missiles, including Man-Portable Air-Defence Systems (MANPADS);
2. Guns, howitzers, and cannons with a calibre greater than 12.7 mm, and ammunition and components specially designed for these, excluding shoulder fired anti-tank rocket launchers, rifle grenades, or grenade launchers;
3. Mortars with a calibre greater than 82 mm;
4. Anti-tank guided weapons, including Anti-tank Guided Missiles (ATGMs) and ammunition and components specially designed for these;
5. Charges and devices containing energetic materials for military use, mines, and related materiel;
6. Weapon sights with a night vision capability.
